Privacy Policy
This is the privacy policy for the mobile app
CardGames.io
("The App"), published by the Icelandic company
Rauðás Games ehf.
("The company").
Your data, and how we use it
The app does not have access to any personal data from you. We store data on your device to remember your scores and preferences
            for the games in the app, we do not send this data to our servers, it's only stored on your device.
We send events to our servers to get aggregated statistics for gameplay, i.e. we may log how many games of Hearts are played by users
            of the app, how many percentage of games the computer players win, how many games are started and finished etc. This data is only saved in an aggregated form,
            we know that all our users together played 5000 games of Hearts today for example, but we have no way of knowing how many games a specific user played.
We don't have access to your name, email address or any other data about you. If you email us for support (
support@cardgames.io
) then we'll
            have your email address but will only ever use it to reply to your emails, we never use it for any other purpose and never share it with any 3rd parties.
Your data and how it is used by our Analytic partners
In addition to aggregate data collected by us as described above, this app utilizes Google Analytics for additional insights in how our users use our app and 
            how we can improve it. This data is collected in aggregate and stored on Google servers. We use Google analytics to measure 
            how many people visit us, how many people play each of our games, how many people visit from each country,
            and other more broken-down diagnosic data than what we collect on our own servers.
Google may utilize personal information in forming the aggregate data, but by the time we get access to the data all personally identifiable 
            information has been stripped away: much like with data we collect we are able to use Google Analytics to see that 4000 people using Chrome 
            visited our site and that on average they spent 20 minutes playing games, but we cannot trace that back to any specific user - all 
            data we are interested in is collected in aggregate and we configure Google Analytics to store as little data about our users as possible.
We prompt our users about our anaytic collection in relevant regions the first time the app is opened. You
            can also later change your mind by clicking on the menu icon in the upper left corner and choosing Ads & Privacy.
Your data and how it's used by our advertising partners
To serve ads within the game we use Google AdMob, an advertising network owned by Google. They use a "device identifer" on your device to serve you personalized ads. A device identifier is
            a unique number that they have access to, which they can use to serve you personalized ads, based on apps or websites you've visited. AdMob may also send requests to 10 other ad
            companies which can then use your device identifier to serve you relevant ads.
For users in the EU and EEA, you will get a prompt when starting the app for the first time, asking whether you want to allow personalized ads, or get non-personalized ones. You
            can also later change your mind by clicking on the menu icon in the upper left corner and choosing Ads & Privacy.
Other ad companies
Below is a list of the ad companies we work with and links to their privacy policies, if you want to better understand how they may use your data.
